%h2
  A Mind for Management

%h4  
  A six-week development programme for line managers

%p
  Strong managers are essential to any successful organisation. A good line manager will motivate staff, increase productivity, and lead happy and effective teams. Excellent managers attract exceptional staff, make you a preferred employer and can be the primary reason for leaving or staying in a company.

%p
  Line managers have a huge impact on the performance and wellbeing of staff. For example, a manager clearly articulating goals can 
  boost discretionary effort by 27.6% 
  %i
    (Hewitt Associates, 2011).
 	Yet 41 per cent of managers and 53 per cent of senior managers are seriously considering leaving their jobs 
  %i
    (Mercer, 2011)
  and many are struggling with increased pressures and the need to ask more of their people. From motivation to innovation, modern managers need to understand management psychology in order to get the best from their teams.

%p
  This six-week programme teaches managers about the psychology of management. It provides practical insights from neuroscience & psychology to help managers support people better and get the best from their teams. Delivered in bite-sized chunks, perfect for high-pressure environments, this is a fresh, innovative approach to develop your managers and help your people work smarter and reach their potential.

%p
  This programme is aimed at anyone with line management responsibilities, particularly new managers, and provides an essential grounding on managing people and developing teams. 

