%h2
  A Mind for Sales

%h4  
  A high-impact four-week programme to give your sales team a lift

%p
  Selling is an emotional business. The pressure to meet targets, maintain pipelines and be the face of the business can have a huge impact on a sales team’s stress levels. Staying positive under pressure, dealing with setbacks, influencing customers, all take a lot of mental energy.

%p
  High-performing sales teams invest in the minds of their people. Research shows that increasing employee wellbeing can 
  increase sales by up to 9% 
  %i
    (IJSIM 14, 2003),
  and employees are 
  12% more productive 
  when in a positive mental state 
  %i
    (Warwick, 2010).

%p
  The Mind for Sales programme introduces all the key psychological components of selling. Delivered at your offices in a series of four engaging, interactive 75-minute masterclasses by experienced trainers, each session tells you what you need to know about how our minds work, and helps you apply this knowledge to how you sell. This is a fresh, innovative approach to help people work smarter and reach their mental potential.

%p
  This programme is aimed at sales teams and their managers, and has been specially designed to give your sales team a lift and enable them to work in a smarter and more sustainable way. 

